  "prompt": "Is it true that Pakistan imports salt from India?",
  "response": "Yes, it is true that Pakistan has, on occasion, imported salt from India. Historically, both countries have engaged in trade for various commodities, including salt. However, the trade dynamics can change based on political relations, border issues, and other factors. It's important to note that most salt production in Pakistan is from its own sources, especially from the Khewra Salt Mine, which is one of the largest and oldest salt mines in the world. Importing salt from India is generally limited and may occur when there are specific supply or quality issues. ",
